{"cursor":"20192","size":14,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n'Brown' or 'Brown people' is a racial and ethnic classification. Like black\npeople and white people, it is a metaphor for race based on human skin color. In\nracialist anthropology, the color brown and the term \"brown people\" was used to\ndescribe a series of hypothesized racial groups that included various\npopulations from North Africa, the Horn of Africa, the Near East, Middle East,\nSouth Asia and Southeast Asia. In Brazil, brown people is a cognate term for\npardo. In North America, both Latinos and South Asians sometimes self-identify,\nor are sometimes described as, brown people.\n\n","linknr":449,"url":"Brown_People","recorded":1362575767,"links":19,"instances":["racial_categorization","classification_of_human_beings","south_africa"],"pdf":["http://as.nyu.edu/docs/IO/1043/S.Asian.Race.ID.JEMS.January.2001.pdf"],"categories":["Race (human classification)","Scientific racism","Social groups","Social issues","Ethnonyms"],"headings":["A category in racialist \"science\"","Ethnic and racial identifier","See also","References","Further reading"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Ambox_question.svg/40px-Ambox_question.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Stoddard_race_map_1920.jpg/300px-Stoddard_race_map_1920.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["race","classification_of_human_beings"],["racialism","racial_categorization"],["racialism","racial_categorization"],["pencil_test","south_africa"]],"members":["racialism","race","pencil_test"],"related":["Race_(classification_of_human_beings)","Ethnic_group","Bla